FILE: tools.rs
MOD: mcp/tools
ROLE: MCP tool definitions — broker_register, broker_send, broker_frame_post, broker_presence, broker_peek, broker_messages, broker_tool_register, broker_tool_list, broker_tool_get, broker_tool_deregister
EP: BrokerTools::new; broker_register; broker_send; broker_frame_post; broker_presence; broker_peek; broker_messages; broker_tool_register; broker_tool_list; broker_tool_get; broker_tool_deregister
STAB: volatile
INV:
  - broker_send constructs an HttpFrame (POST /v1/dms, X-From, X-To) and POSTs via send_raw
  - broker_frame_post constructs an HttpFrame (POST /v1/posts, X-From, X-To) and POSTs via send_raw
  - All network tools (broker_peek, broker_messages, send_raw) send X-Agent-Name header
  - SessionManager holds all credential state — BrokerTools is stateless except for the session Arc
  - broker_register handles 409 (project exists) by loading key from disk — graceful re-registration
  - broker_register accepts optional description param — forwarded to /agents/register; omitted defaults to ""
  - broker_presence includes description suffix " — {desc}" when non-empty; omits when blank
  - send_raw is the single HTTP send path — broker_send and broker_frame_post both route through it
LOOK: send_raw header set; broker_register 409 path; broker_tool_register validation
CHK: cargo build -p mcp after changes
CNTR: mcp/tools::broker_send depends_on mcp/session::SessionManager
